description.plain:
Aaron Carter (December 7, 1987 – November 5, 2022) released his self-titled debut album in 1997. Born and raised in Tampa, Carter starting singing around the age of 7.

Carter released his second album in 2000 titled Aaron’s Party (Come Get It) which ended up selling three million copies.

Over the years, he appeared on Nickelodeon and ended up opening for the Backstreet Boys on a world tour. He’d later release On Aaron and Another Earthquake in later years.

On February 10, 2017, Aaron released his comeback EP titled LøVë.

On November 5, 2022, Carter passed away at the age of 34.

Aaron’s Party (Come Get It) was the title song to Aaron Carter’s sophomore album.

The song peaked at #35 on the Billboard Hot 100 in 2000.

songs.full_title: I Want Candy by Aaron Carter
songs.title: I Want Candy

description.plain:
Aaron Carter released a cover of the classic rock hit “I Want Candy” performed and written by The Strangelove, released in 1965. The song became Carter’s second lead single appearing on his international debut album, Aaron’s Party (Come Get It) released in 2000 on September 26th.

I Want Candy is forever one of Aaron’s biggest hits of all time that fans all around the world love dearly, being a bop. The former pop star put together an EDM version as the official remix, that appeared featuring on his fifth studio record, LØVË, released on February 16th, 2018.
